quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  75,1,"Nay, I swear by the Day of Resurrection;",footnotes:182437:1
  75,2,"and nay, I swear by the self-reproaching soul!",footnotes:182438:1
  75,3,"Does man imagine that We will not be able to bring his bones together again?",footnotes:182439:1
  75,4,"Yes indeed; We have the power to remould even his finger-tips.",footnotes:182440:1
  75,5,"But man desires to persist in his evil ways.",footnotes:182441:1
  75,6,"He asks: “When will the Day of Resurrection be?”",footnotes:182442:1
  75,7,"When the sight is dazed,",footnotes:182443:1
  75,8,"and the moon is eclipsed,"
  75,9,"and the sun and the moon are joined together,",footnotes:182383:1
  75,10,"on that Day will man say: “Whither the refuge?”"